Path: godot/classes/class_foldablecontainer.rst
Summary: This section describes the properties available for the FoldableContainer node, including its group, folded state, language, title, and title text rendering options.

Properties:

foldable_group (FoldableGroup): The FoldableGroup associated with the container. When multiple FoldableContainer nodes share the same group, only one of them is allowed to be unfolded.
Method: set_foldable_group(value: FoldableGroup)
Method: get_foldable_group()

folded (bool): If true, the container will become folded and will hide all its children. Default: false.
Method: set_folded(value: bool)
Method: is_folded()

language (String): Language code used for text shaping algorithms. If left empty, the current locale is used instead. Default: "".
Method: set_language(value: String)
Method: get_language()

title (String): The container's title text. Default: "".
Method: set_title(value: String)
Method: get_title()

title_alignment (HorizontalAlignment): Title's horizontal text alignment. Default: 0.
Method: set_title_alignment(value: HorizontalAlignment)
Method: get_title_alignment()

title_position (TitlePosition): Title's position. Default: 0.
Method: set_title_position(value: TitlePosition)
Method: get_title_position()

title_text_direction (TextDirection): Title text writing direction. Default: 0.
Method: set_title_text_direction(value: TextDirection)
Method: get_title_text_direction()

title_text_overrun_behavior (OverrunBehavior): Defines the behavior of the title when the text is longer than the available space. Default: 0.
Method: set_title_text_overrun_behavior(value: OverrunBehavior)
Method: get_title_text_overrun_behavior()
