Document: FoldableContainer
Path: godot/classes/class_foldablecontainer.rst
Summary: This section describes methods for managing title bar controls and folding/expanding a FoldableContainer.

Method: add_title_bar_control(control: Control) -> void
Adds a Control that will be placed next to the container's title, obscuring the clickable area. Prime usage is adding Button nodes, but it can be any Control. The control will be added as a child of this container and removed from previous parent if necessary. The controls will be placed aligned to the right, with the first added control being the leftmost one.

Method: expand() -> void
Expands the container and emits folding_changed.

Method: fold() -> void
Folds the container and emits folding_changed.

Method: remove_title_bar_control(control: Control) -> void
Removes a Control added with add_title_bar_control(). The node is not freed automatically, you need to use Node.queue_free().
---CHUNK---
Document: FoldableContainer
Path: godot/classes/class_foldablecontainer.rst
Summary: This section describes the theme properties available for customizing the appearance of a FoldableContainer, including colors, fonts, icons, and styleboxes.

Theme Property Descriptions
*   collapsed_font_color (Color): The title's font color when collapsed. Default: Color(1, 1, 1, 1).
*   font_color (Color): The title's font color when expanded. Default: Color(0.875, 0.875, 0.875, 1).
*   font_outline_color (Color): The title's font outline color. Default: Color(1, 1, 1, 1).
*   hover_font_color (Color): The title's font hover color. Default: Color(0.95, 0.95, 0.95, 1).
*   h_separation (int): The horizontal separation between the title's icon and text, and between title bar controls. Default: 2.
*   outline_size (int): The title's font outline size. Default: 0.
*   font (Font): The title's font.
*   font_size (int): The title's font size.
*   expanded_arrow (Texture2D): The title's icon used when expanded.
*   expanded_arrow_mirrored (Texture2D): The title's icon used when expanded (for bottom title).
*   folded_arrow (Texture2D): The title's icon used when folded (for left-to-right layouts).
*   folded_arrow_mirrored (Texture2D): The title's icon used when collapsed (for right-to-left layouts).
*   focus (StyleBox): Background used when FoldableContainer has GUI focus. The focus StyleBox is displayed over the base StyleBox, so a partially transparent StyleBox should be used to ensure the base StyleBox remains visible. A StyleBox that represents an outline or an underline works well for this purpose. To disable the focus visual effect, assign a StyleBoxEmpty resource. Note: Disabling the focus visual effect will harm keyboard/controller navigation usability, so this is not recommended for accessibility reasons.
*   panel (StyleBox): Default background for the FoldableContainer.
*   title_collapsed_hover_panel (StyleBox): Background used when the mouse cursor enters the title's area when collapsed.
*   title_collapsed_panel (StyleBox): Default background for the FoldableContainer's title when collapsed.
*   title_hover_panel (StyleBox): Background used when the mouse cursor enters the title's area when expanded.
*   title_panel (StyleBox): Default background for the FoldableContainer's title when expanded.